[It appears as though there are conflicting reports now on the actual
situation in India. The original posting did suggest the possibility of
overdose of Vitamin A attributable to human error combined with
introduction of a new dispensing measurer. The BBC article in this posting
suggests that the deaths were coincidental in previously ill children who
were given Vitamin A supplement. If there are any ProMED-mail readers with
official information to help clarify this situation, it would be very much
appreciated. - Mod.MPP
